headline.print_headline: Iran, Six Powers Hold 'Useful' Nuclear Talks; Agreement Elusive
headline.main: Iran, Six Powers Hold 'Useful' Nuclear Talks; Agreement Elusive

lead_paragraph: Iran and six world powers held more "useful" talks on Tehran's nuclear program, the European Union announced on Wednesday, as a Western diplomat said they are still struggling to overcome deep disagreements on the future of Iranian atomic capabilities.
